<!-- field-end:crossreference-note -->
<!-- field-end:notes -->
<!-- documentid:15_77yyy  usckey:1500000000077000000000yyy00000000 currentthrough:19910102 documentPDFPage:-1 -->
<!-- itempath:/150/CHAPTER 2A/SUBCHAPTER III/Sec. 77yyy -->
<!-- itemsortkey:150AAHX -->
<!-- expcite:TITLE 15-COMMERCE AND TRADE!@!<usCode chapter="2A" edition="1994" title="15">CHAPTER 2A</usCode>-SECURITIES AND TRUST INDENTURES!@!SUBCHAPTER III-TRUST INDENTURES!@!Sec. 77yyy -->
<!-- field-start:head -->
<h3 class="section-head">§77yyy. Penalties</h3>
<!-- field-end:head -->
<!-- field-start:statute -->
<p class="statutory-body">Any person who willfully violates any provision of this subchapter or any rule, regulation, or order thereunder, or any person who willfully, in any application, report, or document filed or required to be filed under the provisions of this subchapter or any rule, regulation, or order thereunder, makes any untrue statement of a material fact or omits to state any material fact required to be stated therein or necessary to make the statements therein not misleading, shall upon conviction be fined not more than $10,000 or imprisoned not more than five years, or both.</p>
<!-- field-end:statute -->
<!-- field-start:sourcecredit -->
<p class="source-credit">(May 27, 1933, ch. 38, title III, §325, as added <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=53&amp;page=1177" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;" target="_blank">Aug. 3, 1939, ch. 411, <statuteatlarge page="1177" volume="53">53 Stat. 1177</statuteatlarge></a>; amended June 4, 1975, <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=89&amp;page=163" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;" target="_blank"><plaw congress="94" isprivate="false" number="29">Pub. L. 94–29,</plaw> §27(d), <statuteatlarge page="163" volume="89">89 Stat. 163</statuteatlarge></a>.)</p>
<!-- field-end:sourcecredit -->
<!-- field-start:notes -->
<!-- field-start:amendment-note -->
<h4 class="note-head">Amendments</h4>
<p class="note-body"><b>1975</b>—<plaw congress="94" isprivate="false" number="29">Pub. L. 94–29</plaw> substituted "$10,000" for "$5,000".</p>
<!-- field-end:amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:effectivedate-amendment-note -->
<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1975 Amendment</h4>
<p class="note-body">Amendment by <plaw congress="94" isprivate="false" number="29">Pub. L. 94–29</plaw> effective June 4, 1975, see section 31(a) of <plaw congress="94" isprivate="false" number="29">Pub. L. 94–29,</plaw> set out as a note under <uscode edition="1994" section="78b" title="15">section 78b of this title</uscode>.</p>
<!-- field-end:effectivedate-amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:crossreference-note -->
<h4 class="note-head">Cross References</h4>
<p class="note-body">Penalties under—</p>
<p class="note-body-flush2_hang3">Investment Advisers Act of 1940, see <uscode edition="1994" section="80b-17" title="15">section 80b–17 of this title</uscode>.</p>
<p class="note-body-flush2_hang3">Investment Company Act of 1940, see <uscode edition="1994" section="80a-48" title="15">section 80a–48 of this title</uscode>.</p>
<p class="note-body-flush2_hang3">Public Utility Holding Company Act of 1935, see <uscode edition="1994" section="79z-3" title="15">section 79z–3 of this title</uscode>.</p>
<p class="note-body-flush2_hang3">Securities Act of 1933, see <uscode edition="1994" section="77x" title="15">section 77x of this title</uscode>.</p>
<p class="note-body-flush2_hang3">Securities Exchange Act of 1934, see <uscode edition="1994" section="78ff" title="15">section 78ff of this title</uscode>.</p>
<p class="note-body">Rules and regulations, authority of Commission to make, issue, amend and rescind, see <uscode edition="1994" section="77sss" title="15">section 77sss of this title</uscode>.</p>
<p class="note-body">Statements in or omissions from analysis required under <uscode edition="1994" range="77eee to 77ggg" section="77eee" title="15">sections 77eee to 77ggg of this title</uscode>, section as inapplicable to, see <uscode edition="1994" section="77eee" title="15">section 77eee of this title</uscode>.</p>
<!-- field-end:crossreference-note -->
<!-- field-end:notes -->
<!-- field-start:secref -->
<h4 class="note-head">Section Referred to in Other Sections</h4>
<!-- field-end:secref -->
<!-- field-start:sectionreferredto -->
<p class="note-body">This section is referred to in <uscode edition="1994" section="77eee" title="15">section 77eee of this title</uscode>.</p>
<!-- field-end:sectionreferredto -->
<!-- documentid:15_77zzz  usckey:1500000000077000000000zzz00000000 currentthrough:19910102 documentPDFPage:-1 -->
<!-- itempath:/150/CHAPTER 2A/SUBCHAPTER III/Sec. 77zzz -->
<!-- itemsortkey:150AAHY -->
<!-- expcite:TITLE 15-COMMERCE AND TRADE!@!<usCode chapter="2A" edition="1994" title="15">CHAPTER 2A</usCode>-SECURITIES AND TRUST INDENTURES!@!SUBCHAPTER III-TRUST INDENTURES!@!Sec. 77zzz -->
<!-- field-start:head -->
<h3 class="section-head">§77zzz. Effect on existing law</h3>
<!-- field-end:head -->
<!-- field-start:statute -->
<p class="statutory-body">Except as otherwise expressly provided, nothing in this subchapter shall affect (1) the jurisdiction of the Commission under the Securities Act of 1933 [<uscode edition="1994" section="77a" title="15">15 U.S.C. 77a et seq.</uscode>], or the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 [<uscode edition="1994" section="78a" title="15">15 U.S.C. 78a et seq.</uscode>], or the Public Utility Holding Company Act of 1935 [<uscode edition="1994" section="79" title="15">15 U.S.C. 79 et seq.</uscode>], over any person, security, or contract, or (2) the rights, obligations, duties, or liabilities of any person under such acts; nor shall anything in this subchapter affect the jurisdiction of any other commission, board, agency, or officer of the United States or of any State or political subdivision of any State, over any person or security, insofar as such jurisdiction does not conflict with any provision of this subchapter or any rule, regulation, or order thereunder.</p>
<!-- field-end:statute -->
<!-- field-start:sourcecredit -->
<p class="source-credit">(May 27, 1933, ch. 38, title III, §326, as added <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=53&amp;page=1177" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;" target="_blank">Aug. 3, 1939, ch. 411, <statuteatlarge page="1177" volume="53">53 Stat. 1177</statuteatlarge></a>.)</p>
<!-- field-end:sourcecredit -->
<!-- field-start:notes -->
<!-- field-start:referenceintext-note -->
<h4 class="note-head">References in Text</h4>
<p class="note-body">The Securities Act of 1933, referred to in text, is act <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=48&amp;page=74" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;" target="_blank">May 27, 1933, ch. 38, title I, <statuteatlarge page="74" volume="48">48 Stat. 74</statuteatlarge></a>, as amended, which is classified generally to subchapter I (§77a et seq.) of this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see <uscode edition="1994" section="77a" title="15">section 77a of this title</uscode> and Tables.</p>
<p class="note-body">The Securities Exchange Act of 1934, referred to in text, is act <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=48&amp;page=881" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;" target="_blank">June 6, 1934, ch. 404, <statuteatlarge page="881" volume="48">48 Stat. 881</statuteatlarge></a>, as amended, which is classified generally to <uscode chapter="2B" edition="1994" title="15">chapter 2B</uscode> (§78a et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see <uscode edition="1994" section="78a" title="15">section 78a of this title</uscode> and Tables.</p>
<p class="note-body">The Public Utility Holding Company Act of 1935, referred to in text, is act <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=49&amp;page=838" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;" target="_blank">Aug. 26, 1935, ch. 687, title I, <statuteatlarge page="838" volume="49">49 Stat. 838</statuteatlarge></a>, as amended, which is classified generally to <uscode chapter="2C" edition="1994" title="15">chapter 2C</uscode> (§79 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see <uscode edition="1994" section="79" title="15">section 79 of this title</uscode> and Tables.</p>
<!-- field-end:referenceintext-note -->
<!-- field-start:function-transfer-note -->
<h4 class="note-head">Transfer of Functions</h4>
<p class="note-body">For transfer of functions of Securities and Exchange Commission, with certain exceptions, to Chairman of such Commission, see Reorg. Plan No. 10 of 1950, §§1, 2, eff. May 24, 1950, 15 F.R. 3175, <statuteatlarge page="1265" volume="64">64 Stat. 1265</statuteatlarge>, set out under <uscode edition="1994" section="78d" title="15">section 78d of this title</uscode>.</p>
